#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn103"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn103:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 103 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 103 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn103:0.2"
msgid "Kintisutta "
msgstr "Is This What You Think Of Me? "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn103:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. VAR: pisinārāyaṃ → kusinārāyaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn103:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā pisinārāyaṃ viharati baliharaṇe vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Kusināra, in the Forest of Offerings. "

msgctxt "mn103:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn103:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn103:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn103:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn103:2.1"
msgid "“kinti vo, bhikkhave, mayi hoti: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, is this what you think of me? "

msgctxt "mn103:2.2"
msgid "‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, piṇḍapātahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, senāsanahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’”ti? "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama teaches the Dhamma for the sake of robes, alms-food, lodgings, or rebirth in this or that state.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn103:2.3"
msgid "“Na kho no, bhante, bhagavati evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“No sir, we don’t think of you that way.” "

msgctxt "mn103:2.4"
msgid "‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, piṇḍapātahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, senāsanahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti, itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "mn103:2.5"
msgid "“Na ca kira vo, bhikkhave, mayi evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“If you don’t think of me that way, "

msgctxt "mn103:2.6"
msgid "‘cīvarahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn103:2.7"
msgid "itibhavābhavahetu vā samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ desetī’ti; "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: atha kinti carahi vo → atha kinti vo (pts1) | atha kiñcarahi vo (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:2.8"
msgid "atha kinti carahi vo, bhikkhave, mayi hotī”ti? "
msgstr "then what exactly do you think of me?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn103:2.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavati hoti: "
msgstr "“We think of you this way: "

msgctxt "mn103:2.10"
msgid "‘anukampako bhagavā hitesī; "
msgstr "‘The Buddha is compassionate and wants what’s best for us. "

msgctxt "mn103:2.11"
msgid "anukampaṃ upādāya dhammaṃ desetī’”ti. "
msgstr "He teaches out of compassion.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn103:2.12"
msgid "“Evañca kira vo, bhikkhave, mayi hoti: "
msgstr "“So it seems you think "

msgctxt "mn103:2.13"
msgid "‘anukampako bhagavā hitesī; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn103:2.14"
msgid "anukampaṃ upādāya dhammaṃ desetī’ti. "
msgstr "that I teach out of compassion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli2.239, sc3
#. VAR: vo → ye te (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ye vo mayā dhammā abhiññā desitā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "In that case, each and every one of you should train in the things I have taught from my direct knowledge, that is: "

msgctxt "mn103:3.2"
msgid "cattāro satipaṭṭhānā cattāro sammappadhānā cattāro iddhipādā pañcindriyāni pañca balāni satta bojjhaṅgā ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, tattha sabbeheva samaggehi sammodamānehi avivadamānehi sikkhitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right efforts, the four bases of psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven awakening factors, and the noble eightfold path. You should train in these things in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
#. VAR: siyaṃsu → tattha siyuṃ (bj) | siyā (s1) | siyuṃ (s2, s3, km)
msgctxt "mn103:4.1"
msgid "Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ siyaṃsu dve bhikkhū abhidhamme nānāvādā. "
msgstr "As you do so, it may happen that two mendicants disagree about the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5
msgctxt "mn103:5.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

#. VAR: suvacataraṃ → subbacataraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn103:5.2"
msgid "‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato ceva nānaṃ byañjanato ca nānan’ti, tattha yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "‘These two venerables disagree on both the meaning and the phrasing.’ So you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say to them: "

msgctxt "mn103:5.3"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning and the phrasing. "

#. VAR: Tadamināpetaṃ → tadimināpetaṃ (s2, s3, km)
msgctxt "mn103:5.4"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how "

msgctxt "mn103:5.5"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ. "
msgstr "such disagreement on the meaning and the phrasing comes to be. "

msgctxt "mn103:5.6"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti. "
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:5.7"
msgid "Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable among those who side with the other party and say to them: "

msgctxt "mn103:5.8"
msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The venerables disagree on the meaning and the phrasing. "

msgctxt "mn103:5.9"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how "

msgctxt "mn103:5.10"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva nānaṃ, byañjanato ca nānaṃ. "
msgstr "such disagreement on the meaning and the phrasing comes to be. "

msgctxt "mn103:5.11"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti. "
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:5.12"
msgid "Iti duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretabbaṃ, suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretabbaṃ. "
msgstr "So you should remember what has been incorrectly memorized as incorrectly memorized and what has been correctly memorized as correctly memorized. "

msgctxt "mn103:5.13"
msgid "Duggahitaṃ duggahitato dhāretvā suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretvā yo dhammo yo vinayo so bhāsitabbo. "
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, pts-vp-pli2.240, sc4
msgctxt "mn103:6.1"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

msgctxt "mn103:6.2"
msgid "‘imesaṃ kho āyasmantānaṃ atthato hi kho nānaṃ, byañjanato sametī’ti, tattha yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "‘These two venerables disagree on the meaning but agree on the phrasing.’ So you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable and say to them: "

