msgid "‘āyasmantānaṃ kho atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sameti. "
msgstr "‘The venerables agree on both the meaning and the phrasing. "

msgctxt "mn103:8.9"
msgid "Tadamināpetaṃ āyasmanto jānātha—"
msgstr "But the venerables should know that this is how "

msgctxt "mn103:8.10"
msgid "yathā atthato ceva sameti byañjanato ca sameti. "
msgstr "they come to agree on the meaning and the phrasing. "

msgctxt "mn103:8.11"
msgid "Māyasmanto vivādaṃ āpajjitthā’ti. "
msgstr "Please don’t get into a fight about this.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:8.12"
msgid "Iti suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretabbaṃ. "
msgstr "So you should remember what has been correctly memorized as correctly memorized. "

msgctxt "mn103:8.13"
msgid "Suggahitaṃ suggahitato dhāretvā yo dhammo yo vinayo so bhāsitabbo. "
msgstr "Remembering this, you should speak on the teaching and the training. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc7
#. VAR: taritabbaṃ → coditabbaṃ (s1-3, km, mr) | turitabbaṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn103:9.1"
msgid "Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ siyā aññatarassa bhikkhuno āpatti siyā vītikkamo, "
msgstr "As you train in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, one of the mendicants might commit an offense or transgression. "

# NOTE: Punctuation in MS is incorrect: the following iti belongs on this line, as shown in the repetition below.
#. REF: nya10
msgctxt "mn103:10.1"
msgid "tatra, bhikkhave, na codanāya taritabbaṃ. Puggalo upaparikkhitabbo: "
msgstr "In such a case, you should not be in a hurry to accuse them. The individual should be examined like this: "

msgctxt "mn103:10.2"
msgid "‘iti mayhañca avihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa anupaghāto, paro hi puggalo akkodhano anupanāhī adaḷhadiṭṭhī suppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti. "
msgstr "‘I won’t be troubled and the other individual won’t be hurt, for they’re not irritable and hostile. They don’t hold fast to their views, but let them go easily. I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:10.3"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya. "
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc8
msgctxt "mn103:11.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa: "
msgstr "But suppose you think this: "

msgctxt "mn103:11.2"
msgid "‘mayhaṃ kho avihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto, paro hi puggalo kodhano upanāhī adaḷhadiṭṭhī suppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "‘I will be troubled and the other individual will be hurt, for they’re irritable and hostile. However, they don’t hold fast to their views, but let them go easily. I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful. "

msgctxt "mn103:11.3"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—parassa puggalassa upaghāto. "
msgstr "But for the other individual to get hurt is a minor matter. "

msgctxt "mn103:11.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important "

msgctxt "mn103:11.5"
msgid "svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti. "
msgstr "that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:11.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya. "
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc9
msgctxt "mn103:12.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa: "
msgstr "But suppose you think this: "

msgctxt "mn103:12.2"
msgid "‘mayhaṃ kho vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa anupaghāto. Paro hi puggalo akkodhano anupanāhī daḷhadiṭṭhī duppaṭinissaggī, sakkomi cāhaṃ etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "‘I will be troubled but the other individual won’t be hurt, for they’re not irritable and hostile. However, they hold fast to their views, refusing to let go. Nevertheless, I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful. "

msgctxt "mn103:12.3"
msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—mayhaṃ vihesā. "
msgstr "But for me to be troubled is a minor matter. "

msgctxt "mn103:12.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important "

msgctxt "mn103:12.5"
msgid "svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti. "
msgstr "that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:12.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya. "
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, pts-vp-pli2.242, sc10
