msgid "Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ yadidaṃ—mayhañca vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto. "
msgstr "But for me to be troubled and the other individual to get hurt is a minor matter. "

msgctxt "mn103:13.4"
msgid "Atha kho etadeva bahutaraṃ—"
msgstr "It’s more important "

msgctxt "mn103:13.5"
msgid "svāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti. "
msgstr "that I can draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:13.6"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, evamassa, kallaṃ vacanāya. "
msgstr "If that’s what you think, then it’s appropriate to speak to them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14, sc11
msgctxt "mn103:14.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, evamassa: "
msgstr "But suppose you think this: "

msgctxt "mn103:14.2"
msgid "‘mayhañca kho vihesā bhavissati parassa ca puggalassa upaghāto. Paro hi puggalo kodhano upanāhī daḷhadiṭṭhī duppaṭinissaggī, na cāhaṃ sakkomi etaṃ puggalaṃ akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetun’ti. "
msgstr "‘I will be troubled and the other individual will be hurt, for they’re irritable and hostile. And they hold fast to their views, refusing to let go. I cannot draw them away from the unskillful and establish them in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:14.3"
msgid "Evarūpe, bhikkhave, puggale upekkhā nātimaññitabbā. "
msgstr "Don’t underestimate the value of equanimity for such a person. "

# NOTE: Var readings vacisamhara, vacisamsara, vacisankhara: Comm: Vacīsaṃhāroti vacanasañcāro. Imehi kathitaṃ amūsaṃ antaraṃ paveseyya, tumhe imehi idañcidañca vuttāti amūhi kathitaṃ imesaṃ antaraṃ paveseyyāti attho, Tika: Vacanasañcāroti pesuññavasena aññathāvacanupasaṃhāro. The parallel passage is at AN 2.63, where samsara is the MS reading, and adopted by BB there. Comm there gives a completely different explanation: ubhato vacīsaṃsāroti dvīsupi pakkhesu aññamaññaṃ akkosanapaccakkosanavasena saṃsaramānā vācā vacīsaṃsāro. Tika has: Saṃsaramānāti pavattamānā. Despite this, I think the reading samhara makes better sense, as per MN comm.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15, sc12
#. VAR: diṭṭhipaḷāso → diṭṭhipalāso (bj, mr)
#. VAR: vacīsaṃhāro → vacīsaṃsāro (bj) | vacīsaṅkhāro (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn103:15.1"
msgid "Tesañca vo, bhikkhave, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppajjeyya diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi. "
msgstr "As you train in harmony, appreciating each other, without quarreling, mutual tale-bearing might come up, with contempt for each other’s views, resentful, bitter, and exasperated. "

msgctxt "mn103:15.2"
msgid "Tattha ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "In this case you should approach whichever mendicant you think is most amenable among those who side with one party and say to them: "

#. VAR: samaṇo → samāno (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn103:15.3"
msgid "‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, as we were training, mutual tale-bearing came up. If the Ascetic knew about this, would he rebuke it?’ "

msgctxt "mn103:15.4"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say: "

msgctxt "mn103:15.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyāti. "
msgstr "‘Yes, reverend, he would.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:15.6"
msgid "Etaṃ panāvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘But without giving that up, reverend, can one realize extinguishment?’ "

msgctxt "mn103:15.7"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say: "

msgctxt "mn103:15.8"
msgid "‘etaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya na nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘No, reverend, one cannot.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, pts-vp-pli2.243, sc13
msgctxt "mn103:16.1"
msgid "Athāparesaṃ ekatopakkhikānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yaṃ bhikkhuṃ suvacataraṃ maññeyyātha, so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "Then they should approach whichever mendicant they think is most amenable among those who side with the other party and say to them: "

msgctxt "mn103:16.2"
msgid "‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi, taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, as we were training, mutual tale-bearing came up. If the Ascetic knew about this, would he rebuke it?’ "

msgctxt "mn103:16.3"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say: "

msgctxt "mn103:16.4"
msgid "‘yaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññamaññassa vacīsaṃhāro uppanno diṭṭhipaḷāso cetaso āghāto appaccayo anabhiraddhi taṃ jānamāno samaṇo garaheyyāti. "
msgstr "‘Yes, reverend, he would.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:16.5"
msgid "Etaṃ panāvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘But without giving that up, reverend, can one realize extinguishment?’ "

msgctxt "mn103:16.6"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say: "

msgctxt "mn103:16.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammaṃ appahāya na nibbānaṃ sacchikareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘No, reverend, one cannot.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc14
msgctxt "mn103:17.1"
msgid "Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ pare evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "If others should ask that mendicant: "

msgctxt "mn103:17.2"
msgid "‘āyasmatā no ete bhikkhū akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpitā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Were you the venerable who drew those mendicants away from the unskillful and established them in the skillful?’ "

msgctxt "mn103:17.3"
msgid "Sammā byākaramāno, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ byākareyya: "
msgstr "Answering rightly, the mendicant should say: "

msgctxt "mn103:17.4"
msgid "‘idhāhaṃ, āvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃ, tassa me bhagavā dhammaṃ desesi, tāhaṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ abhāsiṃ. "
msgstr "‘Well, reverends, I approached the Buddha. He taught me the Dhamma. After hearing that teaching I explained it to those mendicants. "

msgctxt "mn103:17.5"
msgid "Taṃ te bhikkhū dhammaṃ sutvā akusalā vuṭṭhahiṃsu, kusale patiṭṭhahiṃsū’ti. "
msgstr "When those mendicants heard that teaching they were drawn away from the unskillful and established in the skillful.’ "

msgctxt "mn103:17.6"
msgid "Evaṃ byākaramāno kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu na ceva attānaṃ ukkaṃseti, na paraṃ vambheti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaroti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "Answering in this way, that mendicant doesn’t glorify themselves or put others down. They answer in line with the teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn103:17.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn103:17.8"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn103:17.9"
msgid "Kintisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

